  "prompt": "Is it generally understood that money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally understood that money laundering is illegal.\n\nHere's why:\n\n* **Widespread Laws:** Virtually every developed nation and many developing nations have laws specifically criminalizing money laundering.\n* **International Treaties:** International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force on Money Laundering (FATF) work to establish and promote global standards against money laundering.  These standards are widely adopted.\n* **Media Coverage:** News outlets regularly report on money laundering cases, highlighting the illegal nature of the activity.\n* **Public Awareness:**  While many people may not understand the complexities of money laundering, they generally recognize it as a process to hide ill-gotten gains, and therefore, illegal.\n\nTherefore, it's safe to say that the illegality of money laundering is widely understood.\n",
